Cell.Data: IMPORTANT THINGS TO NOTE ABOUT THIS SPREADSHEET
This spreadsheet contains data which is used to populate various look-up tables ("system tables") as part of the PolicyCenter configuration. These tables are populated once upon creation of a
new PolicyCenter database, using the corresponding *.csv files located in /config/import. During the configuration period, it is a good idea to configure these tables and then save the data
into the /config/import/ directory in your configuration source control so that it will get loaded automatically. To update the system tables after this point, save the appropriate table (Worksheet)
as CSV and then use the import tools to load the CSV into the tables (following the same instructions as used for loading sample data).
Clicking the "Save to CSV" button on a sheet will save the whole Workbook and then save the data in the sheet to a *.csv file (where * = the name of the sheet, such as "roles.csv")
in the same directory as the Workbook. Clicking the "Save All Sheetsâ€¦" button on this Worksheet will save the whole Workbook
and the save every sheet (whose name doesn't begin with #) as CSV.
Importing CSV into a table that already contains data will add new rows and update existing rows (by matching on the entity-id column), but it will not delete rows that exist in the database
but not in the CSV file. (In general, you should probably mark those rows with retired<>0 to indicate a logical delete while leaving the data in the table in case old data continues to
refer to the old values. If you really do want to delete an old row, then you will need to do this separately using SQL delete commands.)
